### :param Syntax

Route parameters are named URL segments prefixed with a colon:

```javascript
app.get('/users/:userId', (req, res) => {
  res.json(req.params); // { userId: '123' }
});
```

### Multiple Parameters

Define multiple dynamic segments:

```javascript
app.get('/users/:userId/posts/:postId', (req, res) => {
  // GET /users/5/posts/42
  console.log(req.params.userId); // '5'
  console.log(req.params.postId); // '42'
});
```

### Optional Parameters

Use `?` to make a parameter optional:

```javascript
app.get('/users/:userId?', (req, res) => {
  if (req.params.userId) {
    // Specific user
  } else {
    // All users
  }
});
```

### Regex in Routes

Use regular expressions for route patterns:

```javascript
app.get(/\/users\/(\d+)/, (req, res) => {
  // Matches /users/123 but not /users/abc
});
```

### Hyphens and Dots

Express automatically parses hyphens and dots as part of the value:

```javascript
app.get('/files/:filename', (req, res) => {
  // GET /files/report.pdf → req.params.filename = 'report.pdf'
});
```

codeExample:
app.get('/products/:category/:id', (req, res) => {
  const { category, id } = req.params;
  const { page, sort } = req.query;
  res.json({ category, id, page, sort });
});
